h3. Summary

The display of time zones in Confluence is inconsistent with [ISO 8601 standards|http://www.iso.org/iso/home/standards/iso8601.htm]. 

h3. Environment
* Confluence 5.9.5

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Go to !https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/files/157679812/Cog.png! > General Configuration
# Go to ADMINISTRATION > System Information
# Look for System Timezone
{panel}
|System Timezone|Australia/Sydney|
{panel}
# Go to User Menu > Profile > Settings
{panel}
|Time zone|Site Default ((GMT+1000) Sydney, Canberra, Melbourne|
{panel}

h3. Expected Results
* System time zone should display as (for when this issue was created)
{panel}
|System Time zone|AEDT Australian Eastern Daylight Time (UTC+11)|
{panel}
* User time zone should display as
{panel}
|System Time zone|AEDT Australian Eastern Daylight Time (UTC+11)|
{panel}

h3. Actual Results
* System Timezone displays as
{panel}
|System Timezone|Australia/Sydney|
{panel}
# User time zone displays as
{panel}
|Time zone|Site Default ((GMT+1000) Sydney, Canberra, Melbourne|
{panel}
 
h3. Notes
Team Calendar also has issues with the display of time zones.

h3.Workaround
No workaround.

